Pledging public transport (MHD) will introduce, on Wednesday, the flea into their ticketing system
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be recorded in the history of Pražský Dopravní podnik (the pragmatic transport agency) as the date on which they will ride in the subway, trams and buses the first passengers, who, instead of having a paper ticket, will have in their pocket an electronic coupon.
At the moment, it is accessible for about one hundred thousand people, owners of the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy a coupon 30 days or 90 days (this will be valid from 1 January 2009) and at the same time have it recorded on their chipboard in the information points and offices of Dopravní podnik (the Transportation Agency), located in the metro stations Muzeum, Můstek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
From yesterday, there is also the possibility to buy the coupons on the Dopravní podnik web pages: www.dpp.cz.
Over four hundred people took advantage of the service in the morning.
Those who will start using the online store can permanently forget the windows at the metro stations, where they had to until now peddle in impatience in long queues in order to get tickets in paper.
Indeed, they will buy their coupon over the Internet and be recorded on their Opencard card in one of the thirteen Městská knihovna (municipal libraries).
"In these points of contact, there is a window available to passengers with trained staff, who will help interested people with internet purchase and, in addition, will record the coupon they purchased on their card," said project spokesman Martin Opatrný.
Next to libraries, it will also be possible to record the electronic coupons on the Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the vestibule of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, recalling the machines to compose tickets and passengers may have already noticed them in the metro stations Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, there should be eighty," said Opatrný.
Auto control the coupon instead of the driver
The machines that will work from tomorrow are easy to use.
Simply insert the Opencard chip card and the coupon previously purchased will register itself on the card.
